reviews.text: Went in for a quick bite with my kids. We sat upstairs. Ambiance and vibe was on point. We all loved the view from upstairs and the string lights added a cute touch. Good was not bad but not great either. We were hungry so we chowed down. We ordered the shrimp quesadillas, basket of tator tots, and a margherita pizza. Prices aren‚Äôt crazy and is a great place to go back to again for a quick bite. Family friendly, servers could be a little more attentive.
Been a while since I‚Äôve been here but the food was pretty good. I gotta go back to get a better feel for it and to get a seat on the patio!
Awesome Caesar Salad! Truly one of the better Caesar Salads I remember getting out of a bar. Their take on the Philly cheesesteak wasn‚Äôt bad either. Great local neighborhood bar.

I recently visited Garaje and it was an incredible experience. The chicken bites were the best I‚Äôve ever had, the beer was delicious, and the Michelangelo sandwich was simply outstanding. Prices are very affordable and the service was perfect. Highly recommended!

We went here after a basketball game, around 3pm on Saturday. Place was busy which I took as a good sign. Atmosphere was great. Sports bar vibes meets family friendly. Food was divine and there was definitely something for everyone. Great place to grab a beer or two.

editorial_summary.overview: Neighborhood hangout with a long beer list, eclectic bar fare, a rooftop deck, TVs & games.

detailedReviews.author: Michael Rutz

detailedReviews.author: Andy Gonzalez
detailedReviews.text: This was my 1st time coming here and the experience was great!!! Nice clean place, friendly staff, cold beer, good food, price wasn't bad at all. Would definitely recommend this spot, as I will definitely be coming back.

detailedReviews.author: James Clark
detailedReviews.text: An hour and a half wait for food while it was slow. No communication from server. Didn't approach server until an hour and got told "hopefully" in a few minutes. Came on a Monday where Martinis were a special and wasn't told from the server. Mobile orders were of importance over dine-in. Would not recommend. The only thing that was a 5 star were my company.

detailedReviews.author: Mona Brendalen
detailedReviews.text: Great little rooftop spot. Really good food with friendly service.

detailedReviews.author: Jillian Kegley
detailedReviews.text: This is a fun and comfortable place to be. It‚Äôs very well run. The beverage program is perfect and appropriate for the spot. We‚Äôve tried several things on the menu and I‚Äôve always been happy. It‚Äôs become our new local favorite.  We get take out often as well.

detailedReviews.author: James Webb
detailedReviews.text: First time coming to this restaurant, food was very good. Nice place to stop in for a quick bite

detailedReviews.author: Elizabeth Foerster
detailedReviews.text: First time coming here in years; order was ready exactly when it said it would be, bartender was prompt and friendly getting me my pick up order. Got buffalo wings-excellent sauce, gooey creamy Mac, and two chicken sandwiches. Even the chips were good and crispy. One of the best meals I‚Äôve had in a long time.

detailedReviews.author: Glenda Anderson
detailedReviews.text: Decent menu, would enjoy a few more brunch options. Good selection of drinks.Nice rooftop for a sunny day. Staff were efficient

Prices aren‚Äôt crazy and is a great place to go back to again for a quick bite. Family friendly, servers could be a little more attentive.

detailedReviews.author: Brigitte
detailedReviews.text: Atmosphere and service was so great. First time being here. I wanted to be in a patio that was away from downtown but had similar lively vibes and this was perfect

detailedReviews.author: g marie
detailedReviews.text: Went there for a work meeting and everything was great! The quesadillas are so good. We only had appetizers and the drinks were great!

detailedReviews.author: Edwin Arteaga
detailedReviews.text: The food was great and friendly service!

detailedReviews.author: Amber Chiquini
detailedReviews.text: Awesome Caesar Salad! Truly one of the better Caesar Salads I remember getting out of a bar. Their take on the Philly cheesesteak wasn‚Äôt bad either. Great local neighborhood bar.

detailedReviews.author: Stacie Bogle
detailedReviews.text:
Came in because the website said they have a mad hatter sandwich with tofu as an option for protein. Didn‚Äôt say how the tofu was made, so I came in to ask. Didn‚Äôt want it to be fried in buttermilk batter. Person taking my order seemed a bit rushed and tried to talk me out of ordering it because they ‚Äúwould have to ask someone‚Äù. It was busy, so I get where they are coming from. After waiting a long time, I was told they don‚Äôt even have tofu. So I left.

Here‚Äôs my thing, make it clear for customers. It‚Äôs 2025! Have a clear and labeled menu- some of us don‚Äôt want to eat dead animals or consume breast milk of another animal. Even the bean burger was on a butter bun. The menu in the restaurant said you could add protein, but didn‚Äôt say what kind of protein was available, the QR code on the menu to ‚Äúshow the full menu‚Äù also didn‚Äôt say what kind of protein you could add. The website did, but apparently there‚Äôs no tofu. Bring back the tofu!

detailedReviews.author: E Grim
detailedReviews.text:
A good place to go. A long list of beers to choose from and the food is pretty good
The balcony area is a great area
No reservations needed

detailedReviews.author: Samantha.cal88 Calderon
detailedReviews.text: Got the mac and cheese empanadas, so yummy. Definitely ask for buffalo sauce with it.

detailedReviews.author: Natasha Monjar
detailedReviews.text: Me and my family go around 1x month. We love the gigantic pretzel and drinks. Their menu is solid, service good and we love love love the patio/rooftop in the summer.

detailedReviews.author: Nate Martin
detailedReviews.text: Cool little local spot! Cold beer and nice folks.

detailedReviews.author: Danielle Papa
detailedReviews.text: Outstanding food every single time we visit! And they always have my tequila and it‚Äôs always the best time!!!!! I cannot stress enough, how good the food is!!!!!!!!!

detailedReviews.author: Ed
detailedReviews.text: The Garage Bar food is really not your average bar fare. It is definitely better quality. Fesh ingredients and I understand, made from scratch. We have had the Cosmic Shrimp Tacos, Carmela, and the Supreme among others. All were incredible! Joint has been busy both visits, servers bust their butts and are attentive and make sure customers are taken care of. We also enjoyed some darts upstairs. We will be back, cannot wait to check out rooftop Bar!

detailedReviews.author: Richard Linked
detailedReviews.text: Great food, good selection, not too bad on drink choices too, and service was quick.

detailedReviews.author: Aris Carlos
detailedReviews.text: If you need somewhere quick to hang out with decent bar food, this is certainly an option.  Also, if you like your tots and fries with that extra crunch, this is it.

detailedReviews.author: Kevin Diver
detailedReviews.text: Love the rooftop.

detailedReviews.author: Giancarlo Peregrina
detailedReviews.text: Friday, February 28th, 2025 at around 6:30pm. I walked in while a group of friends were waiting for me. The place was absolutely packed! And knew right off the bat, there would be a wait. However, Erin was amazing at serving us while working under pressure with the volume of people at the Garage. The food was fresh and very spot on! I‚Äôve been here before and returning again I was not disappointed at all. No complaints here. Definitely returning again for the summer time!

detailedReviews.author: AB Video Chicago
detailedReviews.text: Amazing place,food,customer service and place is very clean‚Ä¶

detailedReviews.author: Alex Magdalene
detailedReviews.text: Great vibe, great food! I was here for a private party upstairs and even though we were away from the main seating area we were given lots of attention. The staff are rock stars!

detailedReviews.author: Megasaur Media LLC
detailedReviews.text: The Garage has been highly recommended by our peers in the community. We had to stop by for some savory burgers and an excellent assortment of beer!

detailedReviews.author: Brian Ahearn
detailedReviews.text: My favorite eatery in Chicago has been the home of important memories here as well as the best food! They also have an upstairs & bands play! This place is fit for a night out or even a quick bite! Tremendous staff!

detailedReviews.author: Molly
detailedReviews.text: Great atmosphere, friendly staff, great time with the DJ. Had an absolute blast. Will be back!

detailedReviews.author: kristin hutson
detailedReviews.text:
Pros: Mac n Cheese, Black Bean Burger, decent offering of Belgiums in bottles
Cons: No IPA on tap, ordered 16 oz bottle of Lindemans priced at $18 and they served me a 12 oz bottle (dropped price to $14 after I said something), they don't have giardinara (it's Chicago), and our server was helpful, but seemed so unhappy I was worried about them the whole time.

detailedReviews.author: Nick Partida
detailedReviews.text: Good food and a comfortable casual ambience. And a nice selection of beers available

detailedReviews.author: Soraya P√©rez
detailedReviews.text: I love this place. They always remember  my son and I. The servers acknowledge you even if they are not your server on a different day!  New servers are attentive also. Drinks are brought promptly. Food is served within reasonable time. The servers come to check on the food quality  and to check for additional drinks! The Buffalo wings are hit with my son. My favorites are shrimp, chicken salad, and waffle fries. They are delivered well cooked and good presentation.  They are very family oriented. I never have to wait more than 10 seconds to be acknowledged and seated. They allow me to get the same table for my son if it's not taken because he  is disabled and prefers sameness. I love the atmosphere on Bingo night! A member of my community recommended this llace as friendly, good drinks and reasonable prices.  The establishment is clean and decorated differently each holiday or season. I could go on and on!

detailedReviews.author: Earnest Dismukes
detailedReviews.text: Great drinks specials didn't try the food so I can speak on that. The place has a great atmosphere, my only gripe is that they closed earlier than I thought they would. Worth it to check this place out I know I'll be back!!! üëçüèøüëçüèø

Food is amazing but the service has been consistently poor the last few visits. Some of the worse service I‚Äôve ever seen. Disappointing because I very much enjoy their food.

detailedReviews.author: Bob Ryan
detailedReviews.text: Excellent

detailedReviews.author: Harley Sexton
detailedReviews.text: My favorite place to go. Matt is the best.

detailedReviews.author: Robert Dennis
detailedReviews.text: Great food and solid drinks make this place. The massive soft pretzel is a must buy item. So good! Attentive staff and great bloody Mary's. Will Def return!

detailedReviews.author: Felicia Peters
detailedReviews.text: Drinks were good and so was the Michelangelo (chicken on focaccia)! Rooftop is also very nice

detailedReviews.author: Karen Pedersen
detailedReviews.text:
Looking for a new place to stop before the Blackhawks game and found The Garage.  Amazing service, our server gave us recommendations that were outstanding.  Had the best burger!!!.  We will be back!
Highly recommend this great neighborhood place.

detailedReviews.author: BIll Kriwko
detailedReviews.text: I‚Äôm never disappointed when I go here the food is really good. The bartenders are real friendly and outgoing and helpful.

detailedReviews.author: Dean Martin
detailedReviews.text: Hannah our server was fantastic. One of our party spilled a drink on herself and she brought water napkins and wet wipes. We are little on the large side so the high top chairs were a little tight so she moved us to a low table no questions asked. The pretzel was great and as advertised enough for 4. Drinks were reasonably priced. The Sandwichs were well priced (for today's standards). Sat on the roof top ...nice view on a beautiful night.

detailedReviews.author: Javier Vargas
detailedReviews.text: Service was good. Sat upstairs but anytime someone started walking on the deck flooring our table and chairs would start moving making  for an uncomfortable visit.

detailedReviews.author: sassy cintron
detailedReviews.text: Food is very delicious service excellent they also have roof top to enjoy the weather

detailedReviews.author: Teresa Groat
detailedReviews.text:
Our server, Maya, was ON IT! Our first time and we will certainly come back.
Roof top was very busy with a large birthday party but the staff rose to the occasion.
So-good food, good service and reasonable prices.

detailedReviews.author: Estevan Calderon
detailedReviews.text: Really good , exelent service , exelent food üëå

detailedReviews.author: Cameron Houseman
detailedReviews.text: I love this place! Great food, awesome service, and close to home. Favorite place in Jefferson Park for sure!

detailedReviews.author: Juan Rios
detailedReviews.text: This is the penultimate neighborhood bar! Featuring ten rotating taps pouring locally made beers and ciders, a large selection of ‚Äúniche‚Äù bottles and cans, and a menu and kitchen that is on par (if not better) than many of the more popular chain restaurants. All served by a talented team of servers and bartenders. Everyone should visit at least once, and I guarantee that you‚Äôll be back!

detailedReviews.author: Mia Powell
detailedReviews.text: My group waited a full hour for our food. Some of us ordered just apps or sides. By time our food actually got here, my tacos were cold (and one-note). The only upside to this experience was our waitress, who was a very sweet woman; the drink service was quick and accurate. It‚Äôs the kitchen that fails here, and the music is too loud to converse.

detailedReviews.author: Erick Gonzalez
detailedReviews.text: Absolutely terrible service. We easily waited over an hour and a half for our food. We ended up leaving, so I couldn‚Äôt tell you how the food was. I‚Äôm sure it was good though. Mind you, these are sandwich‚Äôs we‚Äôre talking about. They say it‚Äôs a kid friendly environment, but if you want your family to wait over an hour and a half for food for food then by all means.

detailedReviews.author: Jake Smith
detailedReviews.text: Love the Garage! It‚Äôs the gem of the neighborhood. Great staff, great food, great drinks. Can‚Äôt beat the roofdeck in the summer

detailedReviews.author: Luis Vazquez
detailedReviews.text: First time here. Always pass this place and finally decided to have dinner. It‚Äôs 2 floors plus the bar on the first floor. We had Pizza, Burger & chicken bites. For drinks I had strawberry mojito and spouse had Margarita. Worth the price. Almost forgot the Elote too.

detailedReviews.author: Dejan Marinkovic
detailedReviews.text: The bar is very nice with garden on it‚Äôs top. Staff is friendly and very fast. The food was delicious, you have too much fries as a side dish. Prices are pretty better than in other parts of Chicago. I would highly recommend.

detailedReviews.author: Will Akhtar
detailedReviews.text: Great staff and food.

detailedReviews.author: Stephen E
detailedReviews.text: Came here for lunch after our church service, and the food was really good. Also we sat on the upstairs patio area and there was a lot of sunlight hitting us and the waiter put down the shade which was really nice. The staff also was very helpful with whatever we needed.
